org.orgName: District Court for the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory

body.p: Territory of Washington, } ss Third Judicial District.
To Elizabeth Pritehard, Jacob Levy, Chas. E. Harding, F.C. Bird, Thos. Morse, Helen Walsh, D.W. Ricard and J.H. Woolery -

In the name of the UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, you are hereby commanded to be and appear at the Chambers of the Judge of the District Court for the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, at Seattle, for the District aforesaid, at 2 o'clock in the afternoon of the 22nd day of August- A.D. 1885 then and there to give evidence in a certain cause therein pending wherein in Re; Application of Plaintiff and Michael Henan for Writ of Habeas Corpus- Defendant, and to remain ni attendance on said Court from day to day threafter until discharged, and herein fail not at your peril.

Witness the HON. ROGER S. GREENE, Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory and Judge of said District Court, this 21st day of August A.D., 1885 JAMES SEAVEY, Clerk. By James Ludlow Deputy.
In the District Court, holding terms at Seattle, Washington Territory.
In re Application of Michael Henan for Habeas Corpus
For Petitioner FILED AUG 22 1885 James Seavey, Clerk. By James Ludlow Deputy Clerk.
Territory of Washington, } ss. County of King

I hereby certify that I served received the within Subpoena on the 22nd day of August A.D. 1885, and personally served the same on Elizabeth Pritehard, Jacob Levy, Chas. E. Harding, F.C. Bird, Thos. Morse, Helen Wash and D.W. Ricard by reading the same to each of them in King County, Washington Territory, on 22nd day of August A.D., 1885
Dated King County, W.T. 22nd day of August A.D. 1885
J.H. McGraw Sheriff By D.R. McKinley Dep
FEES. Serving Subpoena, $2.80 Mileage, Miles, $ .60 Certificate $ .50 $3.90
